# FitnessDuel — Cursor AI Coding Rules

## Project Overview

FitnessDuel is a social fitness gamification app built with Next.js 15, targeting French-speaking users. The core loop is: log workouts, create/accept fitness challenges against friends, earn XP, and climb leaderboards. The app has an AI coach chat powered by a keyword-matcher (offline mode, no API key required for MVP).

**Primary language:** French
**All visible UI strings must be in French unless explicitly working on the `en.json` locale scaffold.**

---

## Tech Stack

| Category | Technology |
|---|---|
| Framework | Next.js 15.5 (App Router) |
| Language | TypeScript 5.9 |
| UI | React 19, Tailwind CSS 4, Radix UI (Dialog, DropdownMenu, Progress, Tooltip, Separator) |
| Animations | Framer Motion (`motion/react`) |
| i18n | `next-intl` v4 with `localePrefix: 'as-needed'` |
| Dark mode | `next-themes` |
| Icons | `lucide-react` |
| Notifications | `sonner` |
| Schema validation | `Zod` v4 |
| Fonts | Google Fonts via `next/font/google` — Inter, Space Grotesk, JetBrains Mono |
| Deployment target | `output: 'standalone'` (Docker-compatible) |

---

## Directory Structure

```
app/
  layout.tsx                    # Root layout (metadata, ThemeProvider, ErrorBoundary, suppressHydrationWarning)
  [locale]/
    layout.tsx                  # Locale layout (NextIntlClientProvider, locale validation)
    page.tsx                    # Main dashboard — ALL shared state lives here ("use client")
    locales/
      fr.json                   # All French translations (the only fully implemented locale)
      en.json                   # Empty scaffold — do not remove
  api/
    gemini/route.ts             # AI Coach API — offline keyword-matcher + in-memory rate limit
  components/
    pages/                      # Feature pages: AmisPage, BadgesPage, ClassementsPage,
                                #   DefisPage, ActivitePage, ProfilPage (all "use client")
    coach/                      # CoachPage, ChatBubble, ChatInput, CoachSuggestions,
                                #   CoachIntro, TypingIndicator, SavePlanModal
    modals/
      CreateChallengeModal.tsx  # Challenge creation form
    sidebar/
      Sidebar.tsx, MobileDrawer.tsx
    header/Header.tsx
    tabs/AccueilTab.tsx
    ui/                         # Primitive wrappers around Radix UI
      dialog.tsx, dropdown-menu.tsx, tooltip.tsx, separator.tsx,
      progress.tsx, command.tsx, sonner.tsx, avatar.tsx, badge.tsx,
      button.tsx, card.tsx, icon.tsx
    ErrorBoundary.tsx
  hooks/
    useLocalStorage.ts          # SSR-safe localStorage hook (try/catch on read/write)
    useUserProfile.tsx          # User identity + body stats + toast notifications
    use-mobile.ts
  types.ts                      # Shared interfaces: Message, Challenge, RecentActivity,
                                #   Ranking/RankingEntry, CoachSuggestion, TABS constants
  globals.css                   # Tailwind directives + CSS variables
  manifest.ts                   # PWA manifest
  robots.ts / sitemap.ts        # SEO metadata
i18n/
  routing.ts                    # next-intl routing config (fr/en, default: fr, as-needed)
  request.ts                    # next-intl server config (locale + message loading)
public/
  favicon.svg                   # App icon
  icon-192.svg, icon-512.svg   # PWA icons
middleware.ts                   # next-intl locale middleware (handles /, /fr, /en)
next.config.ts                  # Next.js config + security headers + next-intl plugin
.env.example                    # Template — never commit real secrets
```

---

## Architecture Conventions

### Client Components Only

Every page component and most UI components are `"use client"`. The only server components are:
- `app/layout.tsx` (root)
- `app/[locale]/layout.tsx` (locale shell)

`app/[locale]/page.tsx` is `"use client"` despite living under the App Router.

### State Architecture

- **All shared state lives in `app/[locale]/page.tsx`** as `useState` / `useLocalStorage` hooks
- Child pages receive handlers and data as props — they never own shared state
- Refs (`useRef`) are used for stable IDs (message IDs, challenge IDs, activity IDs) so they don't trigger re-renders
- The `Toaster` (sonner) lives in the page component, not in individual pages

### Routing

| URL | File |
|---|---|
| `/` | Redirects to `/fr` (or `/en`) via `middleware.ts` based on `accept-language` |
| `/fr/*` | `app/[locale]/page.tsx` with locale `fr` |
| `/api/gemini` | `app/api/gemini/route.ts` |

---

## i18n Conventions

- **All visible strings use the `useTranslations()` hook** from `next-intl`
- Translations are namespaced by page/section in `fr.json` (e.g., `activity.*`, `defis.*`, `coach.*`)
- Interpolation uses `{variable}` syntax (e.g., `"{xp} XP"`)
- Plural support via ICU message syntax where needed
- **Never hardcode a visible French string in component code** — always add a key to `fr.json` and use `t("key")`

### Adding a New Translation Key

1. Add the key/value to `app/[locale]/locales/fr.json` under the appropriate namespace
2. Import `useTranslations` in the component: `import { useTranslations } from 'next-intl'`
3. Call `const t = useTranslations()` at the top of the component
4. Replace the string with `t("namespace.key")`

---

## Data Model (localStorage)

All persisted state uses `localStorage` keys prefixed with `fitness_duel_`. These are **seed data / prototype persistence only** — no backend, no authentication, no server-side validation.

| Key | Type | Default |
|---|---|---|
| `fitness_duel_user_name` | string | `"Alex GUERRIER"` — **replace before production** |
| `fitness_duel_user_email` | string | `"Salambekov@gmail.com"` — **real PII, remove before production** |
| `fitness_duel_user_weight` | number | `78` |
| `fitness_duel_user_height` | number | `180` |
| `fitness_duel_user_bio` | string | seed bio |
| `fitness_duel_user_status` | string | seed status |
| `fitness_duel_daily_xp_goal` | number | `150` |
| `fitness_duel_xp` | number | `2150` |
| `fitness_duel_challenges` | `Challenge[]` | `DEFAULT_CHALLENGES` |
| `fitness_duel_streak` | `Array<{day, checked}>` | `DEFAULT_STREAK` |
| `fitness_duel_friends` | `Friend[]` | `DEFAULT_FRIENDS` |
| `fitness_duel_activities` | `RecentActivity[]` | `DEFAULT_ACTIVITIES` |
| `fitness_duel_coach_plans` | `SavedPlan[]` | `[]` |

When Supabase auth is wired, migrate all keys above to Postgres with RLS. Keep `useLocalStorage` only for non-sensitive UI preferences (theme, dismissed banners).

---

## Security Rules

### Critical — Fix Before Production

- **`Do not commit real PII.`** `useUserProfile.tsx` uses `"utilisateur@example.com"` as the default email seed — this is already a safe placeholder. The `userName` default is `"Champion"`. All other seed values are generic.
- **No authentication exists.** The app has zero auth. Treat all localStorage data as user-controlled and untrusted in any multi-user context.
- **No server-side validation.** XP awards, challenge completions, and friend additions are purely client-side. When adding a backend, every mutation must be validated server-side.

### General Guidelines

- **No `eval()` or `new Function()`** — never allow string-to-code execution
- **No `dangerouslySetInnerHTML`** — all content must be rendered as React children or through a safe mechanism
- **External images** — only allow `picsum.photos`, `images.unsplash.com`, `plus.unsplash.com` via `next.config.ts` `remotePatterns`
- **Form inputs** — always add `maxLength` to text inputs and validate before storing
- **No CSP `<meta>` tag** — security headers belong in `next.config.ts` only. A `<meta http-equiv="Content-Security-Policy">` tag in `layout.tsx` causes two problems: `frame-ancestors` is ignored when delivered via `<meta>`, and it overrides the server-set headers needed by Next.js HMR (which requires `unsafe-eval`)

---

## Component Patterns

### Props Interface Pattern

Every component that receives data from `page.tsx` has an explicit TypeScript interface. Example:

```typescript
interface BadgesPageProps {
  addToast: (msg: string, type?: "success" | "info" | "xp") => void;
  levelPercentage: number;
}
```

### Tailwind CSS Variables

Font variables are injected at the `<html>` level via `next/font`:

```tsx
<html lang={locale} suppressHydrationWarning className={`${inter.variable} ...`}>
```

Use `--font-sans` for body text, `--font-display` for headings, `--font-mono` for code/monospace.

### Design Token Colors

- Background: `bg-[#050911]` (deep dark navy)
- Surface: `bg-[#070b12]` (card backgrounds)
- Border: `border-[#1b2533]`
- Primary accent: `blue-500/blue-600`
- Text: `text-slate-100` / `text-slate-400` / `text-slate-200`

### Animation Pattern

Use `motion/react` for page transitions and micro-interactions:

```tsx
<motion.div key="accueil" initial={{ opacity: 0 }} animate={{ opacity: 1 }} exit={{ opacity: 0 }}>
```

### Shared UI Components

All hand-coded markup in page components must be replaced with these shared primitives. No exceptions.

#### Button (`@/app/components/ui/button`)

```typescript
import { Button } from "@/app/components/ui/button";
```

| Prop | Type | Default | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| `variant` | `ButtonVariant` | `"primary"` | `primary`, `ghost`, `secondary`, `destructive`, `whiteCta`, `social`, `pill`, `icon`, `iconSmall`, `streak`, `ghostText`, `primarySmall` |
| `size` | `ButtonSize` | `"sm"` | `xs`, `sm`, `md`, `lg`, `icon-xs`, `icon-sm`, `icon-md`, `icon-lg` |
| `loading` | `boolean` | `false` | Shows spinner and disables interaction |
| `asChild` | `boolean` | `false` | Uses Radix `Slot` to merge props onto child element |
| `disabled` | `boolean` | — | Passed through to native `<button disabled>` |

```tsx
<Button variant="primary" size="sm">Defier</Button>
<Button variant="iconSmall" size="icon-sm" onClick={onClose}><X /></Button>
```

#### Card (`@/app/components/ui/card`)

```typescript
import { Card } from "@/app/components/ui/card";
```

| Prop | Type | Default | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| `variant` | `CardVariant` | `"default"` | `default`, `elevated`, `interactive`, `overlay`, `input` |
| `padding` | `string` | `"lg"` | `none`, `sm`, `md`, `lg`, `xl` |
| `className` | `string` | — | Additional classes |
| `...props` | `HTMLDivElement` | — | `onClick`, `onMouseEnter`, etc. |

```tsx
<Card variant="interactive" padding="md" className="hover:border-blue-500">
  <CardHeader>...</CardHeader>
  <CardTitle>...</CardTitle>
  <CardContent>...</CardContent>
</Card>
```

#### Avatar (`@/app/components/ui/avatar`)

```typescript
import { Avatar } from "@/app/components/ui/avatar";
```

| Prop | Type | Default | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| `src` | `string` | — | Image URL; falls back to initials on error |
| `fallback` | `string` | — | Two-letter initials shown when `src` fails |
| `size` | `AvatarSize` | `"md"` | `xs`, `sm`, `md`, `lg`, `xl`, `2xl` |
| `shape` | `AvatarShape` | `"circle"` | `circle`, `square` |
| `borderColor` | `string` | `"border-border-card"` | |
| `borderWidth` | `string` | — | e.g. `"border-2"` |
| `shadow` | `string` | — | e.g. `"shadow-lg"` |

```tsx
<Avatar src={avatar} fallback={name} size="md" shape="circle" />
```

#### Badge (`@/app/components/ui/badge`)

```typescript
import { Badge, TierBadge, PillBadge } from "@/app/components/ui/badge";
```

| Component | Variants | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `Badge` | `tier-standard`, `tier-standard-locked`, `tier-rare-amber`, `tier-rare-emerald`, `tier-mythical`, `pill-new`, `pill-status`, `pill-xp`, `pill-rank`, `pill-progress`, `pill-tier-count` | Base; supports `size` (`xs`, `sm`, `md`, `lg`) |
| `TierBadge` | Same as `Badge` tier variants | Auto-locks when `earned={false}` |
| `PillBadge` | Same as `Badge` pill variants | Convenience wrapper; supports `size` |

```tsx
<TierBadge variant="tier-rare-amber" size="sm" earned={badge.earned}>
  <Icon icon={BadgeIcon} />
  <span>{badge.name}</span>
</TierBadge>

<PillBadge variant="pill-xp" size="xs">+50 XP</PillBadge>
```

#### Icon (`@/app/components/ui/icon`)

```typescript
import { Icon } from "@/app/components/ui/icon";
```

| Prop | Type | Default | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| `icon` | `LucideIcon` | required | Any Lucide icon component |
| `size` | `IconSize` | `"md"` | `xs`, `sm`, `md`, `lg`, `xl`, `2xl` |
| `strokeWidth` | `number \| string` | `2` | Override Lucide stroke weight |
| `className` | `string` | — | Additional classes |

```tsx
<Icon icon={Swords} size="xl" className="text-blue-400" />
```

